      "writtenOn": "2021-06-23T20:21:50Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "This seems like a good optimization, since it limits the pixels we need to touch. When the view matrix is scale+translate and the clip is a rect, both fillRectToRect and fillPixelsWithLocalMatrix should go through attemptQuadOptimization, which would then result in roughly equivalent geometry as the conservative bounds.\n\nWhen the clip is complex or the view matrix is complex, that optimization won\u0027t happen and we only crop the geometry if it\u0027s excessively large. For drawPaint, it makes sense to be as tight as possible.",
